    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Empiric treatment of bacterial meningitis in adults over 50 years of age must cover Streptococcus pneumoniae, Neisseria meningitidis, Listeria monocytogenes, and aerobic gram-negative bacilli."
    },
